Parliament, Tuesday, 15 October 2019 – As part of its three-day oversight visit to Eskom in the Gauteng Province, the Standing Committee on Appropriations (SCOA) will tomorrow engage with the group executive of human resources (HR) on HR-related challenges in Eskom, as well as the impact of dismissals and termination of contracts on its business.
	
	The committee will also meet with the general manager of procurement to discuss, amongst other things, non-compliance and the challenges and costs associated with long-term contracts.
	
	The programme is as follows:
